因為作惡的必被剪除，唯有等候耶和華的必承受地土。(詩篇 37:9) For the wicked will be destroyed, but those who trust in the Lord will possess the land. (Psalm 37:9)
當止住怒氣，離棄憤怒，不要心懷不平，以致作惡。(詩篇 37:8) Stop being angry! Turn from your rage! Do not lose your temper— it only leads to harm. (Psalm 37:8)
你當默然倚靠耶和華，耐性等候他，不要因那道路通達的和那惡謀成就的心懷不平。(詩篇 37:7)
他要使你的公義如光發出，使你的公平明如正午。(詩篇 37:6)
He will make your innocence radiate like the dawn, and the justice of your cause will shine like the noonday sun. (Psalm 37:6)
當將你的事交託耶和華，並倚靠他，他就必成全。(詩篇 37:5) Commit everything you do to the Lord. Trust him, and he will help you. (Psalm 37:5)
又要以耶和華為樂，他就將你心裡所求的賜給你。(詩篇 37:4) Take delight in the Lord, and he will give you your heart’s desires. (Psalm 37:4)
你當倚靠耶和華而行善，住在地上，以他的信實為糧。(詩篇 37:3) Trust in the Lord and do good. Then you will live safely in the land and prosper. (Psalm 37:3)
不要為作惡的心懷不平，也不要向那行不義的生出嫉妒。因為他們如草快被割下，又如青菜快要枯乾。(詩篇 37:1-2)
願你常施慈愛給認識你的人，常以公義待心裡正直的人。-詩篇 36:10 Pour out your unfailing love on those who love you; give justice to those with honest hearts.-Psalm 36:10
因為在你那裡有生命的源頭，在你的光中我們必得見光。(詩篇 36:9) For you are the fountain of life, the light by which we see. (Psalm 36:9)
You feed them from the abundance of your own house, letting them drink from your river of delights. (Psalm 36:8)
他們必因你殿裡的肥甘得以飽足，你也必叫他們喝你樂河的水。(詩篇 36:8)
你的公義好像高山，你的判斷如同深淵。耶和華啊，人民、牲畜你都救護。(詩篇 36:6)
耶和華啊，你的慈愛上及諸天，你的信實達到穹蒼。(詩篇 36:5)
惡人的罪過，在他心裡說：「我眼中不怕神。」(詩篇 36:1) Sin whispers to the wicked, deep within their hearts. They have no fear of God at all. (Psalm 36:1)
我的舌頭要終日論說你的公義，時常讚美你。(詩篇 35:28) Then I will proclaim your justice, and I will praise you all day long.(Psalm 35:28)
Don’t let my treacherous enemies rejoice over my defeat. Don’t let those who hate me without cause gloat over my sorrow.(Psalm 35:19)
我的骨頭都要說：「耶和華啊，誰能像你，救護困苦人脫離那比他強壯的，救護困苦窮乏人脫離那搶奪他的？」(詩篇 35:10)
惡必害死惡人，恨惡義人的必被定罪。(詩篇 34:21) Calamity will surely overtake the wicked, and those who hate the righteous will be punished.(Psalm 34:21)
義人多有苦難，但耶和華救他脫離這一切，又保全他一身的骨頭，連一根也不折斷。(詩篇 34:19-20)
耶和華靠近傷心的人，拯救靈性痛悔的人。(詩篇 34:18) The Lord is close to the brokenhearted; he rescues those whose spirits are crushed. (Psalm 34:18)
But the Lord turns his face against those who do evil; he will erase their memory from the earth. (Psalm 34:16)
耶和華的眼目看顧義人，他的耳朵聽他們的呼求。(詩篇 34:15) The eyes of the Lord watch over those who do right; his ears are open to their cries for help.(Psalm 34:15)
要離惡行善，尋求和睦，一心追趕。(詩篇 34:14) Turn away from evil and do good. Search for peace, and work to maintain it. (Psalm 34:14)
就要禁止舌頭不出惡言，嘴唇不說詭詐的話。(詩篇 34:13) Then keep your tongue from speaking evil and your lips from telling lies! (Psalm 34:13)
Even strong young lions sometimes go hungry, but those who trust in the Lord will lack no good thing. (Psalm 34:10)
你們要嘗嘗主恩的滋味，便知道他是美善。投靠他的人有福了！(詩篇 34:8) Taste and see that the Lord is good. Oh, the joys of those who take refuge in him! (Psalm 34:8)
耶和華的使者在敬畏他的人四圍安營，搭救他們。(詩篇 34:7) For the angel of the Lord is a guard; he surrounds and defends all who fear him. (Psalm 34:7)
我這困苦人呼求，耶和華便垂聽，救我脫離一切患難。(詩篇 34:6) In my desperation I prayed, and the Lord listened; he saved me from all my troubles. (Psalm 34:6)
我曾尋求耶和華，他就應允我，救我脫離了一切的恐懼。(詩篇 34:4) I prayed to the Lord, and he answered me. He freed me from all my fears. (Psalm 34:4)
你們和我當稱耶和華為大，一同高舉他的名。(詩篇 34:3) Come, let us tell of the Lord’s greatness; let us exalt his name together. (Psalm 34:3)
我要時時稱頌耶和華，讚美他的話必常在我口中。(詩篇 34:1) I will praise the Lord at all times. I will constantly speak his praises. (Psalm 34:1)
我們的心向來等候耶和華，他是我們的幫助，我們的盾牌。(詩篇 33:20) We put our hope in the Lord. He is our help and our shield. (Psalm 33:20)
耶和華的眼目看顧敬畏他的人和仰望他慈愛的人，(詩篇 33:18) But the Lord watches over those who fear him, those who rely on his unfailing love. (Psalm 33:18)
What joy for the nation whose God is the Lord, whose people he has chosen as his inheritance. (Psalm 33:12)
耶和華的籌算永遠立定，他心中的思念萬代常存。(詩篇 33:11) But the Lord’s plans stand firm forever; his intentions can never be shaken. (Psalm 33:11)
願全地都敬畏耶和華，願世上的居民都懼怕他。(詩篇 33:8) Let the whole world fear the Lord, and let everyone stand in awe of him. (Psalm 33:8)
The Lord merely spoke, and the heavens were created. He breathed the word, and all the stars were born. (Psalm 33:6)
惡人必多受苦楚，唯獨倚靠耶和華的，必有慈愛四面環繞他。。(詩篇 32:10) Many sorrows come to the wicked, but unfailing love surrounds those who trust the Lord. (Psalm 32:10)
For you are my hiding place; you protect me from trouble. You surround me with songs of victory. (Psalm 32:7)
我向你陳明我的罪，不隱瞞我的惡。我說「我要向耶和華承認我的過犯」，你就赦免我的罪惡。(詩篇 32:5)
我閉口不認罪的時候，因終日唉哼而骨頭枯乾。(詩篇 32:3) When I refused to confess my sin, my body wasted away, and I groaned all day long. (Psalm 32:3)
Yes, what joy for those whose record the Lord has cleared of guilt, whose lives are lived in complete honesty! (Psalm 32:2)
得赦免其過、遮蓋其罪的，這人是有福的！(詩篇 32:1) Oh, what joy for those whose disobedience is forgiven, whose sin is put out of sight! (Psalm 32:1)
凡仰望耶和華的人，你們都要壯膽，堅固你們的心！。(詩篇 31:24) So be strong and courageous, all you who put your hope in the Lord! (Psalm 31:24)
耶和華的聖民哪，你們都要愛他！耶和華保護誠實人，足足報應行事驕傲的人。(詩篇 31:23)
In panic I cried out, “I am cut off from the Lord!” But you heard my cry for mercy and answered my call for help. (Psalm 31:22)
敬畏你、投靠你的人，你為他們所積存的，在世人面前所施行的恩惠是何等大呢！(詩篇 31:19)
求你使你的臉光照僕人，憑你的慈愛拯救我。(詩篇 31:16) Let your favor shine on your servant. In your unfailing love, rescue me. (Psalm 31:16)
我終身的事在你手中，求你救我脫離仇敵的手和那些逼迫我的人。(詩篇 31:15) My future is in your hands. Rescue me from those who hunt me down relentlessly. (Psalm 31:15)
耶和華啊，我仍舊倚靠你，我說：「你是我的神！」(詩篇 31:14) But I am trusting you, O Lord, saying, “You are my God!” (Psalm 31:14)
我被人忘記，如同死人，無人記念，我好像破碎的器皿。(詩篇 31:12) I am ignored as if I were dead, as if I were a broken pot. (Psalm 31:12)
I am dying from grief; my years are shortened by sadness. Sin has drained my strength; I am wasting away from within. (Psalm 31:10)
因為你是我的巖石，我的山寨，所以求你為你名的緣故，引導我，指點我—詩篇 31:3 You are my rock and my fortress. For the honor of your name, lead me out of this danger.—Psalm 31:3
Turn your ear to listen to me; rescue me quickly. Be my rock of protection, a fortress where I will be safe. (Psalm 31:2)
O Lord, I have come to you for protection; don’t let me be disgraced. Save me, for you do what is right. (Psalm 31:1)
耶和華啊，求你應允我，憐恤我！耶和華啊，求你幫助我！」(詩篇 30:10) Hear me, Lord, and have mercy on me. Help me, O Lord.” (Psalm 30:10)
Your favor, O Lord, made me as secure as a mountain. Then you turned away from me, and I was shattered. (Psalm 30:7)
因為他的怒氣不過是轉眼之間，他的恩典乃是一生之久，一宿雖然有哭泣，早晨便必歡呼。(詩篇 30:5)
耶和華啊，你曾把我的靈魂從陰間救上來，使我存活，不至於下坑。-詩篇 30:3 You brought me up from the grave, O Lord. You kept me from falling into the pit of death.-Psalm 30:3
耶和華我的神啊，我曾呼求你，你醫治了我。(詩篇 30:2) O Lord my God, I cried to you for help, and you restored my health. (Psalm 30:2)
耶和華必賜力量給他的百姓，耶和華必賜平安的福給他的百姓。(詩篇 29:11) The Lord gives his people strength. The Lord blesses them with peace.(Psalm 29:11)
神的眾子啊，你們要將榮耀、能力歸給耶和華，歸給耶和華！(詩篇 29:1) Honor the Lord, you heavenly beings; honor the Lord for his glory and strength. (Psalm 29:1)
Save your people! Bless Israel, your special possession. Lead them like a shepherd, and carry them in your arms forever.(Psalm 28:9)
耶和華是我的力量，是我的盾牌，我心裡倚靠他，就得幫助。所以我心中歡樂，我必用詩歌頌讚他。(詩篇 28:7)
不要把我和惡人並作孽的一同除掉，他們與鄰舍說和平話，心裡卻是奸惡。(詩篇 28:3)
Listen to my prayer for mercy as I cry out to you for help, as I lift my hands toward your holy sanctuary. (Psalm 28:2)
I pray to you, O Lord, my rock. Do not turn a deaf ear to me. For if you are silent, I might as well give up and die. (Psalm 28:1)
